  </sponsors>
  <source>Medivation, Inc.</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is being conducted to determine the safety and tolerability of Dimebon in people
      with Huntington's disease after short-term exposure (one week) and after longer exposure
      (three months). Also, the study will assess whether or not there is an effect of Dimebon on
      the symptoms of Huntington's disease, including cognitive (thinking abilities), motor
      (movement), behavior, and overall functioning.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
